WEBVTT - https://subtitletools.com

00:00:03.640 --> 00:00:06.180
Hi everyone! I'm Jamie.

00:00:06.180 --> 00:00:09.280
I'm your Community Relations Facilitator in Callahan, and

00:00:09.280 --> 00:00:11.880
today I'm going to show you how to recycle in the residence halls.

00:00:12.060 --> 00:00:15.180
Your trash and your cardboards will be outside.

00:00:15.180 --> 00:00:18.560
Your recycling will go in the recycling station

00:00:18.560 --> 00:00:21.620
that's located in the first floor lobby.

00:00:21.620 --> 00:00:24.320
Most of your recycling will be in these bins.

00:00:25.340 --> 00:00:27.760
Paper and paper boards

00:00:27.760 --> 00:00:30.300
like these, can go in the bins.

00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:34.200
You can also recycle bottles, cans, and jugs.

00:00:34.880 --> 00:00:37.220
Just make sure they're clean

00:00:37.220 --> 00:00:39.220
and nothing is inside.

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:43.760
Corrugated cardboard and trash go outside.

00:00:47.960 --> 00:00:49.440
Corrugated cardboard is

00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:50.860
a thicker kind of cardboard.

00:00:50.860 --> 00:00:52.860
It has a wavy middle layer.

00:00:52.860 --> 00:00:54.860
It needs to be flattened

00:00:54.860 --> 00:00:56.860
and thrown in the cardboard dumpster.

00:00:59.260 --> 00:01:01.700
There are some things that can't be recycled,

00:01:01.700 --> 00:01:03.700
like pizza boxes with grease or food inside.

00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:05.700
They have to go into the trash.

00:01:06.820 --> 00:01:09.200
Plastic containers that aren't shaped like

00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:11.680
bottles or jugs can't be recycled.

00:01:11.680 --> 00:01:13.680
They also have to go into the trash.

00:01:16.100 --> 00:01:19.100
If you have any questions,

00:01:19.100 --> 00:01:21.100
refer to the UHDS website

00:01:21.100 --> 00:01:22.300
or ask your hall's staff members.

00:01:22.300 --> 00:01:23.840
Thank you for helping us recycle

00:01:23.960 --> 00:01:27.280
and making the halls nicer for everyone to live in.
